1
00:01:49,060 --> 00:01:54,580
=Eight Hundred=

2
00:01:59,820 --> 00:02:00,660
All set.

3
00:02:01,060 --> 00:02:01,900
Here you go.

4
00:02:46,540 --> 00:02:48,020
Sir? Housekeeping.

5
00:02:48,020 --> 00:02:48,860
May I come in?

6
00:02:50,140 --> 00:02:51,020
Sir?

7
00:02:51,020 --> 00:02:52,100
Housekeeping.

8
00:02:52,100 --> 00:02:52,940
May I come in?

9
00:02:59,740 --> 00:03:00,580
Search the room.

10
00:03:17,620 --> 00:03:19,220
(126 Fanyu Road)

11
00:03:25,260 --> 00:03:26,620
Chief Guo, we found a bag of cash.

12
00:03:28,980 --> 00:03:29,980
Catalog everything.

13
00:03:30,420 --> 00:03:31,860
Leave someone here to keep watch.

14
00:03:31,860 --> 00:03:33,180
If Tian Jinhai comes back,

15
00:03:33,180 --> 00:03:34,060
he must not slip away!

16
00:03:34,260 --> 00:03:35,100
Yes, sir.

17
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:35,940
Chief Guo.

18
00:03:35,940 --> 00:03:36,780
The receptionist

19
00:03:36,780 --> 00:03:37,860
just reported something.

20
00:03:37,860 --> 00:03:38,780
Tian Jinhai would

21
00:03:38,780 --> 00:03:40,180
leave a letter at the front desk

22
00:03:40,180 --> 00:03:41,300
to be mailed the next day.

23
00:03:41,300 --> 00:03:42,580
He'd retrieve the letter later on.

24
00:03:42,580 --> 00:03:44,460
I always pick up the mail at this time.

25
00:03:44,460 --> 00:03:45,500
How could you do that?

26
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:46,660
He was wearing your uniform.

27
00:03:46,660 --> 00:03:47,540
He said you took the day off.

28
00:03:47,540 --> 00:03:48,700
So I gave him the mail.

29
00:03:48,700 --> 00:03:50,100
Because of the uniform?

30
00:03:50,100 --> 00:03:51,420
Don't you verify their ID?

31
00:03:51,420 --> 00:03:52,280
Well, why did he have

32
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:53,150
your uniform?

33
00:03:53,260 --> 00:03:54,140
What's going on?

34
00:03:54,740 --> 00:03:55,610
A fake postman

35
00:03:55,610 --> 00:03:57,220
took our mail.

36
00:03:57,220 --> 00:03:58,090
What about the letter?

37
00:03:58,090 --> 00:03:59,580
The letter left by
the guest in room 306?

38
00:03:59,580 --> 00:04:00,460
He took it too.

39
00:04:01,820 --> 00:04:03,460
Was it that guy we saw on our way in?

40
00:04:03,460 --> 00:04:04,300
Yes.

41
00:04:04,660 --> 00:04:05,660
Hou, go after him!

42
00:04:07,220 --> 00:04:08,060
Hello.

43
00:04:08,060 --> 00:04:09,020
We're the municipal PSB.

44
00:04:09,580 --> 00:04:10,780
We'll handle your situation.

45
00:04:10,780 --> 00:04:11,620
Don't worry.

46
00:04:12,060 --> 00:04:12,940
Thank you, officers.

47
00:04:13,380 --> 00:04:14,220
Chief Guo.

48
00:04:14,940 --> 00:04:15,780
He got away?

49
00:04:18,220 --> 00:04:19,060
Director Chen.

50
00:04:19,460 --> 00:04:20,860
We might need you to stick around.

51
00:04:21,140 --> 00:04:21,980
No problem.

52
00:04:21,980 --> 00:04:22,820
It's my duty.

53
00:04:22,820 --> 00:04:23,660
Limin.

54
00:04:23,660 --> 00:04:24,820
Take him to the guesthouse

55
00:04:24,820 --> 00:04:25,690
and get him a room.

56
00:04:25,690 --> 00:04:26,540
- Got it.
- Okay.

57
00:04:26,540 --> 00:04:27,380
I'll head out then.

58
00:04:27,380 --> 00:04:28,220
Chief Guo.

59
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:29,980
I just remembered

60
00:04:30,420 --> 00:04:32,020
that Director Chen and I were chatting,

61
00:04:32,620 --> 00:04:33,780
and he mentioned that

62
00:04:33,780 --> 00:04:34,700
Tian Jinhai took a taxi

63
00:04:35,540 --> 00:04:36,380
to visit him.

64
00:04:37,060 --> 00:04:37,900
It's a long way

65
00:04:38,140 --> 00:04:39,100
from the city

66
00:04:39,100 --> 00:04:40,020
to Fengyang,

67
00:04:40,020 --> 00:04:41,180
yet he took a taxi.

68
00:04:41,180 --> 00:04:42,300
Does that mean

69
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:44,340
he usually takes taxis in the city?

70
00:04:44,340 --> 00:04:45,180
That makes sense.

71
00:04:45,540 --> 00:04:46,380
Tell you what.

72
00:04:46,740 --> 00:04:47,580
I'll have the team

73
00:04:47,580 --> 00:04:48,980
check all the taxis in the city.

74
00:04:49,460 --> 00:04:50,660
You and Director Chen

75
00:04:50,660 --> 00:04:52,570
stay in the city for now
and wait for my update.

76
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:53,820
- Stay in touch.
- Will do.

77
00:04:54,220 --> 00:04:55,060
Let's go, Master.

78
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:24,980
=Episode 16=
(Stranger's Path)

79
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:39,340
Master.

80
00:05:40,260 --> 00:05:42,660
There are only three hospitals
left in the city.

81
00:05:44,740 --> 00:05:45,580
You're tired?

82
00:05:45,900 --> 00:05:46,740
I'm not tired.

83
00:05:46,740 --> 00:05:47,620
No way I'd be tired.

84
00:05:50,620 --> 00:05:51,860
After we check these last three,

85
00:05:53,140 --> 00:05:54,300
we should go back and rest.

86
00:05:55,180 --> 00:05:56,020
It's fine.

87
00:05:56,020 --> 00:05:57,260
With Chief Liu missing,

88
00:05:57,260 --> 00:05:58,500
I'm anxious too.

89
00:05:59,220 --> 00:06:00,660
Where could she be?

90
00:06:02,220 --> 00:06:04,700
And who is by her side right now?

91
00:06:04,700 --> 00:06:06,460
She's a cop.

92
00:06:06,460 --> 00:06:07,420
Think about it.

93
00:06:07,420 --> 00:06:09,580
If she really didn't
want us to find her,

94
00:06:09,580 --> 00:06:10,620
she'd have ways to do so.

95
00:06:11,420 --> 00:06:12,820
She called me yesterday,

96
00:06:12,820 --> 00:06:14,420
and I don't know why.

97
00:06:15,020 --> 00:06:16,980
The call connected,
but she didn't say anything.

98
00:06:16,980 --> 00:06:18,540
And when I tried to call her back,

99
00:06:19,100 --> 00:06:20,220
she wouldn't answer.

100
00:06:21,060 --> 00:06:22,940
It's still the same now.

101
00:06:22,940 --> 00:06:24,300
If it's like you said,

102
00:06:24,700 --> 00:06:26,820
and she doesn't want us to bother her,

103
00:06:28,020 --> 00:06:29,660
she would have just turned off her phone.

104
00:06:37,140 --> 00:06:37,980
Chief Guo.

105
00:06:40,380 --> 00:06:42,420
I'm with Director Chen right now.

106
00:06:44,820 --> 00:06:45,770
Alright.

107
00:06:45,770 --> 00:06:46,620
Okay, sure.

108
00:06:46,620 --> 00:06:47,460
Got it.

109
00:06:47,460 --> 00:06:48,390
Jinshui Road, right?

110
00:06:48,510 --> 00:06:49,580
Okay, I'll head there now.

111
00:06:50,820 --> 00:06:51,660
Master,

112
00:06:51,740 --> 00:06:52,660
I'm really sorry.

113
00:06:52,660 --> 00:06:54,300
Chief Guo wants me
to go to Jinshui Road.

114
00:06:54,300 --> 00:06:56,180
He said Tian Jinhai
was last seen around there.

115
00:06:58,780 --> 00:06:59,700
Jinshui Road?

116
00:07:01,060 --> 00:07:02,220
Hui's rented place

117
00:07:02,220 --> 00:07:03,780
is right around there.

118
00:07:03,780 --> 00:07:04,740
Tian Jinhai has been

119
00:07:04,740 --> 00:07:06,180
in close contact with Hui lately.

120
00:07:07,540 --> 00:07:08,460
There are some things

121
00:07:09,060 --> 00:07:10,940
we really need to ask him about.

122
00:07:11,340 --> 00:07:12,340
I'll go with you.

123
00:07:32,780 --> 00:07:33,660
Chief Guo.

124
00:07:33,660 --> 00:07:34,520
Director Chen.

125
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:35,420
Is this it?

126
00:07:35,420 --> 00:07:36,260
Right here.

127
00:07:36,940 --> 00:07:37,780
Chief Guo,

128
00:07:37,980 --> 00:07:39,380
would it be okay for me to join you?

129
00:07:39,780 --> 00:07:40,620
It's fine.

130
00:07:40,620 --> 00:07:41,620
When we question him,

131
00:07:41,620 --> 00:07:42,780
you can wait in the yard.

132
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:44,540
Alright.

133
00:07:45,540 --> 00:07:46,380
Chief Guo,

134
00:07:46,380 --> 00:07:47,260
someone's coming out.

135
00:07:47,260 --> 00:07:48,390
Songge! Are you home?

136
00:07:50,940 --> 00:07:51,940
Limin?

137
00:07:53,780 --> 00:07:54,620
Mr. Chen?

138
00:07:54,620 --> 00:07:55,750
What are you guys...

139
00:08:01,180 --> 00:08:02,040
We need to ask you

140
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:03,460
and Chen Hui a few questions.

141
00:08:03,460 --> 00:08:04,660
We hope you can cooperate.

142
00:08:06,420 --> 00:08:07,260
Alright.

143
00:08:07,620 --> 00:08:08,780
Tian Jinhai and I

144
00:08:08,780 --> 00:08:10,500
met in Jin'gang.

145
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:12,340
He kept saying he was from overseas.

146
00:08:12,340 --> 00:08:13,740
Only later did I find out

147
00:08:13,740 --> 00:08:14,820
he wasn't at all.

148
00:08:14,820 --> 00:08:17,040
At the time, he wanted
to sell his roller skating rink,

149
00:08:17,300 --> 00:08:19,980
but business was slow,
and no one wanted to take it.

150
00:08:19,980 --> 00:08:21,260
So he gave me

151
00:08:21,260 --> 00:08:22,380
all the old equipment

152
00:08:22,380 --> 00:08:23,300
as a stake

153
00:08:23,300 --> 00:08:24,580
in my rink in Fengyang.

154
00:08:24,580 --> 00:08:26,420
About a year or so later,

155
00:08:26,420 --> 00:08:28,460
I bought him out completely.

156
00:08:28,460 --> 00:08:30,820
We hadn't spoken in over three years.

157
00:08:30,820 --> 00:08:32,980
He didn't come here
just for us this time.

158
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:34,700
He's in the clothing business now.

159
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:36,420
He's in the mainland
to survey the market.

160
00:08:36,420 --> 00:08:37,740
He dropped by to see Chen Hui

161
00:08:37,740 --> 00:08:38,610
and catch up.

162
00:08:38,610 --> 00:08:40,100
Director Chen
from the Fengyang Police Station

163
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:42,300
said Tian Jinhai arrived
over half a month ago.

164
00:08:42,300 --> 00:08:44,140
He's stayed here for this long.

165
00:08:44,140 --> 00:08:46,020
Was it really
just to catch up with you guys?

166
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:49,100
I'm not too sure about that.

167
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:50,300
When he first arrived,

168
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:51,940
Chen Hui's grandfather
had just passed away.

169
00:08:51,940 --> 00:08:54,340
So we didn't really get to talk much.

170
00:08:54,340 --> 00:08:55,900
He was just waiting for us

171
00:08:55,900 --> 00:08:57,460
to finish dealing with the funeral.

172
00:08:58,460 --> 00:09:00,660
I heard the day Tian Jinhai
went to Fengyang,

173
00:09:00,660 --> 00:09:01,940
you rushed back overnight.

174
00:09:01,940 --> 00:09:02,780
What was that about?

175
00:09:02,860 --> 00:09:04,940
Well, we hadn't talked in years.

176
00:09:04,940 --> 00:09:07,580
When I opened the internet cafe,
he showed up out of nowhere.

177
00:09:07,580 --> 00:09:09,700
I was pretty surprised too.

178
00:09:09,700 --> 00:09:10,940
But I was so busy that day,

179
00:09:10,940 --> 00:09:13,220
I didn't even get to chat with him.

180
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:14,700
He cares a lot about face.

181
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:15,860
Without even telling me,

182
00:09:15,860 --> 00:09:17,500
he went to visit my parents.

183
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:19,220
He even brought gifts.

184
00:09:19,220 --> 00:09:20,380
When I heard he went there,

185
00:09:20,380 --> 00:09:21,900
I was actually really happy.

186
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:23,500
I went to see him right away.

187
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:24,540
When was the last time

188
00:09:25,140 --> 00:09:26,010
you saw Tian Jinhai?

189
00:09:26,010 --> 00:09:26,860
Yesterday afternoon.

190
00:09:26,860 --> 00:09:27,770
He came to see us.

191
00:09:28,220 --> 00:09:29,110
What for?

192
00:09:29,540 --> 00:09:31,370
It was just about some business stuff.

193
00:09:31,540 --> 00:09:32,380
He asked us

194
00:09:32,380 --> 00:09:34,350
if we wanted to be
the northern general agents

195
00:09:34,350 --> 00:09:35,540
for his clothing brand.

196
00:09:35,540 --> 00:09:36,860
We don't know much

197
00:09:36,860 --> 00:09:38,180
about clothing brands,

198
00:09:38,180 --> 00:09:39,580
so we haven't agreed to it yet.

199
00:09:39,580 --> 00:09:41,020
About what time did he leave?

200
00:09:41,020 --> 00:09:43,580
When he left, it was probably

201
00:09:43,580 --> 00:09:44,580
around 3 PM.

202
00:09:55,780 --> 00:09:56,650
Master.

203
00:09:56,650 --> 00:09:57,580
They say young people

204
00:09:57,580 --> 00:09:58,420
lack life experience.

205
00:09:59,420 --> 00:10:00,260
Look.

206
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:01,500
The weather is so cold.

207
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:02,940
No plants can survive here.

208
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:22,780
What are you doing, Master?

209
00:10:23,300 --> 00:10:24,620
This dirt has just been turned.

210
00:10:27,860 --> 00:10:28,860
Which means,

211
00:10:29,660 --> 00:10:31,300
these flowers were recently planted.

212
00:10:33,680 --> 00:10:35,260
And Tian Jinhai still hasn't been found.

213
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:44,740
It's the flowerbed.

214
00:10:46,220 --> 00:10:47,500
Find some shovels and dig it up.

215
00:10:47,700 --> 00:10:48,540
Okay.

216
00:11:36,340 --> 00:11:37,660
Why dig such a huge hole?

217
00:11:39,620 --> 00:11:40,980
We were going to build a fish pond.

218
00:11:42,180 --> 00:11:43,500
Why did you plant flowers instead?

219
00:11:43,980 --> 00:11:45,020
It was bad for feng shui.

220
00:11:45,620 --> 00:11:46,460
Who told you that?

221
00:11:47,820 --> 00:11:49,340
Someone in an online chat room.

222
00:11:52,580 --> 00:11:53,420
Chief Guo.

223
00:11:53,740 --> 00:11:54,860
We've hit solid earth.

224
00:11:54,860 --> 00:11:55,740
There's nothing here.

225
00:11:57,460 --> 00:11:59,140
If you're still not satisfied,

226
00:11:59,140 --> 00:12:00,380
look around our place and see

227
00:12:00,380 --> 00:12:01,460
what else you can dig up.

228
00:12:01,900 --> 00:12:03,060
Watch your tone.

229
00:12:05,540 --> 00:12:06,980
You said that Tian Jinhai came to you

230
00:12:06,980 --> 00:12:07,980
with a business proposal.

231
00:12:08,540 --> 00:12:09,740
What's the clothing brand

232
00:12:09,740 --> 00:12:10,580
he's representing?

233
00:12:15,460 --> 00:12:16,300
What?

234
00:12:16,660 --> 00:12:17,740
You don't even know the name

235
00:12:17,740 --> 00:12:18,580
of his brand?

236
00:12:24,580 --> 00:12:25,500
This Tian Jinhai,

237
00:12:26,140 --> 00:12:27,500
he doesn't actually have a brand.

238
00:12:27,940 --> 00:12:29,740
He makes knock-offs of big brands

239
00:12:29,740 --> 00:12:31,180
and uses the "imported" gimmick

240
00:12:31,180 --> 00:12:32,580
to sell them at a premium.

241
00:12:32,580 --> 00:12:34,380
That's illegal.

242
00:12:34,380 --> 00:12:35,460
Of course I said no.

243
00:12:46,620 --> 00:12:47,490
What?

244
00:12:47,490 --> 00:12:48,340
I'll be right there.

245
00:12:49,820 --> 00:12:50,660
Stop digging.

246
00:12:50,660 --> 00:12:51,720
Get in the car, let's go.

247
00:12:51,900 --> 00:12:52,740
Chief Guo,

248
00:12:52,900 --> 00:12:53,900
should we leave one here?

249
00:12:53,900 --> 00:12:54,750
No need.

250
00:12:54,750 --> 00:12:55,820
Tian Jinhai has been found.

251
00:12:56,020 --> 00:12:56,860
He's been found?

252
00:12:57,260 --> 00:12:58,100
Let's go.

253
00:14:42,740 --> 00:14:43,860
Director Chen.

254
00:14:43,860 --> 00:14:45,340
Is this Tian Jinhai?

255
00:14:46,420 --> 00:14:47,260
It's him.

256
00:14:48,420 --> 00:14:49,260
Tang.

257
00:14:49,260 --> 00:14:50,310
Any findings at the scene?

258
00:14:50,660 --> 00:14:51,530
Chief Guo.

259
00:14:51,530 --> 00:14:53,100
Looking at the scene,

260
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:54,620
he has strangulation marks on his neck.

261
00:14:54,620 --> 00:14:55,900
The marks basically match

262
00:14:55,900 --> 00:14:56,740
that triangle.

263
00:14:57,820 --> 00:14:58,660
Impossible.

264
00:15:00,380 --> 00:15:01,740
Chief Liu has late-stage cancer.

265
00:15:02,660 --> 00:15:03,980
She's too weak to strangle him.

266
00:15:05,940 --> 00:15:07,980
Tian Jinhai smells heavily of alcohol.

267
00:15:07,980 --> 00:15:09,260
He probably drank a lot,

268
00:15:09,620 --> 00:15:11,100
which led to a loss of motor control.

269
00:15:11,860 --> 00:15:13,100
As for the exact cause of death,

270
00:15:13,100 --> 00:15:14,410
we'll only know after an autopsy.

271
00:15:14,620 --> 00:15:16,060
Can you determine the time of death?

272
00:15:17,060 --> 00:15:19,460
Between 24 to 48 hours ago.

273
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:20,500
It's just an estimate.

274
00:15:21,940 --> 00:15:23,820
Is the time of death the same
for both of them?

275
00:15:25,660 --> 00:15:26,820
Based on the livor mortis,

276
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:28,340
they are the same.

277
00:15:29,300 --> 00:15:30,140
Director Chen,

278
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:31,140
any thoughts?

279
00:15:32,700 --> 00:15:33,780
It's been so long.

280
00:15:35,420 --> 00:15:36,700
Why weren't they found sooner?

281
00:15:37,140 --> 00:15:38,020
(Cautious)
There are no houses

282
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:39,140
near this road.

283
00:15:39,700 --> 00:15:41,580
Besides those maintaining
the railway bridge,

284
00:15:41,580 --> 00:15:42,740
no one else comes here.

285
00:15:43,180 --> 00:15:44,540
The maintenance crew found them.

286
00:15:46,700 --> 00:15:47,540
Alright then.

287
00:15:47,540 --> 00:15:48,980
Let's all pitch in.

288
00:15:48,980 --> 00:15:50,540
Split up and ask around the village.

289
00:15:50,540 --> 00:15:52,060
See if there are any witnesses.

290
00:15:52,060 --> 00:15:54,220
Once the scene investigation is done,
we'll pack up.

291
00:15:54,620 --> 00:15:55,460
Got it.

292
00:16:16,100 --> 00:16:17,500
(My illness)

293
00:16:17,500 --> 00:16:18,740
can't be cured anymore.

294
00:16:20,660 --> 00:16:22,340
(This should be the last case I take.)

295
00:16:22,980 --> 00:16:24,060
(I have to)

296
00:16:24,060 --> 00:16:24,980
(see it through.)

297
00:16:25,860 --> 00:16:26,740
(Let me enjoy)

298
00:16:26,740 --> 00:16:27,860
(the fun of working.)

299
00:16:30,620 --> 00:16:31,580
(Now I think,)

300
00:16:32,100 --> 00:16:33,500
not only is this place interesting,

301
00:16:34,140 --> 00:16:35,300
you're quite interesting too.

302
00:16:35,300 --> 00:16:36,140
Me?

303
00:16:37,260 --> 00:16:38,140
I'm interesting?

304
00:16:40,940 --> 00:16:41,780
(Chief Liu.)

305
00:16:42,980 --> 00:16:43,820
Someone...

306
00:16:45,180 --> 00:16:46,020
Chief Liu.

307
00:16:46,020 --> 00:16:46,880
Someone

308
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:47,910
wants to

309
00:16:48,300 --> 00:16:49,940
tell you something.

310
00:16:50,660 --> 00:16:51,500
Tell me what?

311
00:16:51,820 --> 00:16:52,660
(If possible,)

312
00:16:53,380 --> 00:16:54,900
(I'd like to help you one last time.)

313
00:16:55,580 --> 00:16:56,740
Do you really believe

314
00:16:57,580 --> 00:16:58,580
it's Hui?

315
00:17:22,540 --> 00:17:24,820
Chen Hui!

316
00:17:24,820 --> 00:17:26,740
I know you're in there!

317
00:17:26,740 --> 00:17:27,620
Come out here!

318
00:17:31,900 --> 00:17:32,760
Mr. Chen!

319
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:33,810
- Let him go!
- Back off!

320
00:17:35,260 --> 00:17:36,100
Tell me!

321
00:17:36,540 --> 00:17:37,660
How did Liu Na die?

322
00:17:38,060 --> 00:17:38,900
How did she die?

323
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:40,940
Liu Na is dead?

324
00:17:41,900 --> 00:17:42,740
How would I know?

325
00:17:42,980 --> 00:17:43,900
You don't know?

326
00:17:45,740 --> 00:17:47,540
Tian Jinhai is your friend.

327
00:17:47,540 --> 00:17:48,980
He and Liu Na didn't know each other.

328
00:17:48,980 --> 00:17:49,840
So how could those two

329
00:17:49,840 --> 00:17:50,830
end up dying together?

330
00:17:50,980 --> 00:17:51,820
How?

331
00:17:52,220 --> 00:17:53,260
Give me an explanation!

332
00:17:53,260 --> 00:17:54,420
Explain what?

333
00:17:54,420 --> 00:17:55,780
What does it have to do with me?

334
00:17:55,780 --> 00:17:57,020
Nothing to do with you?

335
00:17:57,300 --> 00:17:58,140
Right before

336
00:17:58,700 --> 00:17:59,540
Liu Na died,

337
00:17:59,540 --> 00:18:00,900
she called me.

338
00:18:01,260 --> 00:18:02,660
She told me on the phone

339
00:18:02,660 --> 00:18:04,420
that someone wanted to talk to me.

340
00:18:04,860 --> 00:18:06,060
Was that person you?

341
00:18:06,420 --> 00:18:07,260
Or was it you?

342
00:18:09,980 --> 00:18:10,820
Mr. Chen,

343
00:18:11,660 --> 00:18:13,860
let's calm down and talk this out.

344
00:18:13,860 --> 00:18:15,460
Could you let go of Chen Hui first?

345
00:18:15,460 --> 00:18:16,820
We're all family here.

346
00:18:16,820 --> 00:18:17,700
Family?

347
00:18:18,820 --> 00:18:20,380
This house

348
00:18:20,380 --> 00:18:21,500
is haunted!

349
00:18:22,900 --> 00:18:24,220
Would you believe anything I say?

350
00:18:24,700 --> 00:18:25,540
I don't believe you.

351
00:18:25,540 --> 00:18:27,410
Whether it was you or not,
we'll find out soon!

352
00:18:27,410 --> 00:18:28,260
Move!

353
00:18:37,860 --> 00:18:38,700
What are you doing?

354
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:39,700
Dad, what are you doing?

355
00:18:39,700 --> 00:18:40,540
Come with me!

356
00:18:40,980 --> 00:18:42,420
Why did you drag me here?

357
00:18:42,420 --> 00:18:43,260
Dad!

358
00:18:43,700 --> 00:18:44,540
Call the cops.

359
00:18:45,220 --> 00:18:46,420
You're being ridiculous!

360
00:18:47,740 --> 00:18:49,420
Hello.

361
00:18:49,420 --> 00:18:50,340
I'd like to ask...

362
00:18:51,340 --> 00:18:53,060
A guy pretended
to be a postman today.

363
00:18:53,060 --> 00:18:53,900
Which of you saw him?

364
00:18:54,740 --> 00:18:55,580
I saw him.

365
00:18:55,940 --> 00:18:56,860
It was you, right?

366
00:18:56,860 --> 00:18:57,720
Yes.

367
00:18:57,720 --> 00:18:58,740
Then tell me,

368
00:18:58,740 --> 00:18:59,860
what did he look like?

369
00:19:02,660 --> 00:19:04,340
About his height and build.

370
00:19:04,340 --> 00:19:06,540
But he was wearing a mask,
so I couldn't really tell.

371
00:19:07,220 --> 00:19:08,460
How did he sound?

372
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:10,300
He just sounded normal.

373
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:12,740
Here, say a few words to her.

374
00:19:13,380 --> 00:19:14,620
Say something to her!

375
00:19:14,620 --> 00:19:15,580
Say something!

376
00:19:15,580 --> 00:19:16,460
Are you crazy?

377
00:19:16,460 --> 00:19:18,620
Will you only be satisfied
when you put me behind bars?

378
00:19:19,740 --> 00:19:20,730
Say something to her!

379
00:19:20,730 --> 00:19:21,600
- What's wrong?
- What do you want me to say?

380
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:22,740
- Say something!
- It was me!

381
00:19:22,740 --> 00:19:23,600
Happy now?

382
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:24,660
Are you satisfied?

383
00:19:28,540 --> 00:19:29,660
What's all the yelling?

384
00:19:29,660 --> 00:19:30,520
Who called the police?

385
00:19:31,140 --> 00:19:32,020
I did.

386
00:19:32,020 --> 00:19:32,860
Is it these two?

387
00:19:33,460 --> 00:19:34,300
Let's go.

388
00:19:34,300 --> 00:19:35,140
Come with us.

389
00:19:35,620 --> 00:19:36,810
Listen to me, officer...

390
00:19:36,810 --> 00:19:37,860
Hold on.

391
00:19:37,860 --> 00:19:39,340
Save it for the station.

392
00:19:39,780 --> 00:19:40,620
Yes, sir.

393
00:19:49,860 --> 00:19:54,180
(Mediator)

394
00:19:56,940 --> 00:19:57,980
Director Chen,

395
00:19:57,980 --> 00:19:59,980
you have much more experience than I do,

396
00:19:59,980 --> 00:20:01,060
but let me be blunt.

397
00:20:01,820 --> 00:20:02,820
Whether it's work

398
00:20:02,820 --> 00:20:04,340
or family matters,

399
00:20:04,340 --> 00:20:06,620
try to use the right approach.

400
00:20:06,620 --> 00:20:07,620
Don't be so hot-headed.

401
00:20:08,740 --> 00:20:09,580
Got it.

402
00:20:10,540 --> 00:20:11,420
Can I go now?

403
00:20:13,060 --> 00:20:13,940
Sign here first.

404
00:20:16,620 --> 00:20:18,820
(Mediation Agreement)

405
00:20:18,820 --> 00:20:19,660
Hello.

406
00:20:19,660 --> 00:20:21,340
I'm Chen Hongbing
and Chen Hui's family member.

407
00:20:21,340 --> 00:20:22,500
I was called to pick them up.

408
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:24,340
Ding Yue.

409
00:20:24,500 --> 00:20:25,340
Over here.

410
00:20:25,420 --> 00:20:26,260
(Service Window)
Where's Hui?

411
00:20:26,260 --> 00:20:27,100
Mom.

412
00:20:29,420 --> 00:20:30,290
Hui, what...

413
00:20:30,290 --> 00:20:31,460
What happened to your neck?

414
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:34,740
Chen Hongbing,

415
00:20:34,740 --> 00:20:35,700
what is going on?

416
00:20:35,700 --> 00:20:36,660
What do you mean?

417
00:20:36,740 --> 00:20:37,580
You...

418
00:20:37,580 --> 00:20:38,450
Mom.

419
00:20:38,450 --> 00:20:39,340
Why are you here?

420
00:20:40,100 --> 00:20:41,420
Director Tong called me,

421
00:20:41,420 --> 00:20:42,900
and I rushed right over.

422
00:20:43,380 --> 00:20:44,260
Are you okay?

423
00:20:44,260 --> 00:20:45,100
I'm fine.

424
00:20:45,100 --> 00:20:45,940
Don't worry.

425
00:20:46,740 --> 00:20:47,580
I'll head back first.

426
00:20:48,660 --> 00:20:49,500
You and Dad

427
00:20:49,500 --> 00:20:50,340
should head back too.

428
00:20:58,260 --> 00:20:59,100
Did you hit Hui?

429
00:21:01,420 --> 00:21:02,300
Chen Hongbing,

430
00:21:02,300 --> 00:21:03,660
what exactly are you trying to do?

431
00:21:03,980 --> 00:21:04,860
Why are you

432
00:21:04,860 --> 00:21:06,260
so relentless with Hui?

433
00:21:06,260 --> 00:21:07,700
You already brought him in

434
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:08,560
and detained him.

435
00:21:08,560 --> 00:21:09,620
Did you find anything?

436
00:21:09,620 --> 00:21:11,260
Why are you being so unreasonable?

437
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:12,850
I'm not talking about reason today.

438
00:21:12,850 --> 00:21:13,810
What do you mean?

439
00:21:13,810 --> 00:21:14,730
What do I mean?

440
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:15,740
Liu Na is dead.

441
00:21:19,660 --> 00:21:20,740
What did you say?

442
00:21:26,100 --> 00:21:27,100
Liu Na is dead.

443
00:21:37,540 --> 00:21:38,380
Director Chen.

444
00:21:38,820 --> 00:21:39,780
(Here lies Liu Na)
The autopsy results are out.

445
00:21:40,740 --> 00:21:42,900
Chief Liu died of natural causes
due to her illness.

446
00:21:43,380 --> 00:21:45,020
Tian Jinhai died of asphyxiation.

447
00:21:46,980 --> 00:21:47,820
I understand.

448
00:21:51,580 --> 00:21:52,660
It's about time.

449
00:21:52,660 --> 00:21:53,680
Let's begin the ceremony.

450
00:21:59,420 --> 00:22:00,780
It's a tradition in our bureau.

451
00:22:00,780 --> 00:22:01,980
It's ceremonial.

452
00:22:07,740 --> 00:22:10,260
[Here lies Liu Na]
Officer 6512451.

453
00:22:10,260 --> 00:22:11,620
Please respond if you copy.

454
00:22:13,100 --> 00:22:15,820
Officer 6512451.

455
00:22:15,820 --> 00:22:17,060
Please respond if you copy.

456
00:22:18,620 --> 00:22:21,220
Officer 6512451.

457
00:22:21,220 --> 00:22:22,580
Please respond if you copy.

458
00:22:24,660 --> 00:22:27,100
Officer 6512451.

459
00:22:27,100 --> 00:22:28,420
Please respond if you copy.

460
00:22:30,860 --> 00:22:33,460
Officer 6512451.

461
00:22:33,460 --> 00:22:34,580
Please respond if you copy.

462
00:22:37,580 --> 00:22:39,820
Officer 6512451.

463
00:22:40,300 --> 00:22:41,460
Farewell.

464
00:22:41,860 --> 00:22:43,980
- Farewell.
- Farewell.

465
00:22:44,540 --> 00:22:49,900
- Farewell.
- Farewell.

466
00:22:51,900 --> 00:22:52,740
Salute.

467
00:23:04,060 --> 00:23:04,900
Na.

468
00:23:06,780 --> 00:23:07,620
Farewell.

469
00:23:11,580 --> 00:23:13,940
Badge number 6512451

470
00:23:14,380 --> 00:23:15,660
is permanently retired.

471
00:23:37,100 --> 00:23:38,900
We don't even know
what happened to Liu Na.

472
00:23:42,180 --> 00:23:43,500
I couldn't save her.

473
00:23:53,860 --> 00:23:54,740
I'm worried...

474
00:23:57,500 --> 00:23:59,220
that one day,

475
00:24:00,740 --> 00:24:02,860
I won't even be able to save my own son.

476
00:24:03,620 --> 00:24:05,020
What nonsense are you talking about?

477
00:24:05,020 --> 00:24:06,500
Why bring up Hui?

478
00:24:33,500 --> 00:24:34,340
Take a rest.

479
00:24:34,340 --> 00:24:35,220
I'll go make dinner.

480
00:24:39,820 --> 00:24:40,660
Hongbing.

481
00:24:42,740 --> 00:24:43,580
Hongbing?

482
00:24:45,640 --> 00:24:46,820
I want to be alone for a bit.

483
00:24:49,140 --> 00:24:50,660
I'll call you when dinner is ready.

484
00:25:30,460 --> 00:25:31,300
Hongbing.

485
00:25:32,060 --> 00:25:32,900
Time to eat.

486
00:25:36,420 --> 00:25:37,260
Hongbing.

487
00:25:38,100 --> 00:25:39,500
Even if you won't come out,

488
00:25:40,460 --> 00:25:41,780
could you at least say something?

489
00:25:46,140 --> 00:25:46,980
Hongbing?

490
00:26:03,140 --> 00:26:03,980
(Hui.)

491
00:26:04,940 --> 00:26:06,300
(Your dad)

492
00:26:06,300 --> 00:26:08,060
(has locked himself in his room)

493
00:26:08,060 --> 00:26:09,180
(for two days now.)

494
00:26:10,420 --> 00:26:11,260
He won't eat.

495
00:26:11,860 --> 00:26:12,700
And he won't talk.

496
00:26:13,780 --> 00:26:14,900
What are we going to do?

497
00:26:15,780 --> 00:26:16,620
Mom.

498
00:26:17,490 --> 00:26:19,140
I don't know
what to do right now either.

499
00:26:20,740 --> 00:26:21,580
Then can you...

500
00:26:22,180 --> 00:26:24,100
Can you come home and see your dad?

501
00:26:25,060 --> 00:26:25,940
After all,

502
00:26:26,580 --> 00:26:28,380
we are a family.

503
00:26:28,380 --> 00:26:29,380
With you gone,

504
00:26:30,020 --> 00:26:30,900
I'm all alone.

505
00:26:31,740 --> 00:26:33,740
I have no one to talk to.

506
00:26:35,260 --> 00:26:36,860
I don't know what to do anymore.

507
00:26:37,460 --> 00:26:38,380
Mom, don't cry.

508
00:26:39,420 --> 00:26:40,260
Okay.

509
00:26:40,260 --> 00:26:41,580
I'll be right there.

510
00:26:41,580 --> 00:26:42,460
Stop crying.

511
00:26:42,980 --> 00:26:44,980
Okay.

512
00:26:56,980 --> 00:26:57,820
Hongbing!

513
00:26:57,980 --> 00:26:58,820
Open the door,

514
00:26:59,100 --> 00:27:00,140
or I'm kicking it down!

515
00:27:00,820 --> 00:27:01,660
Mom.

516
00:27:02,420 --> 00:27:03,290
Mr. Tong.

517
00:27:03,290 --> 00:27:04,140
Hui.

518
00:27:04,260 --> 00:27:05,380
Hui, do something.

519
00:27:05,490 --> 00:27:06,390
Your dad

520
00:27:06,390 --> 00:27:07,400
- won't come out.
- What are you doing?

521
00:27:07,410 --> 00:27:08,270
Come out here!

522
00:27:08,700 --> 00:27:09,540
Dad!

523
00:27:10,820 --> 00:27:11,660
Dad.

524
00:27:12,820 --> 00:27:13,660
Dad!

525
00:27:14,740 --> 00:27:15,580
Hongbing!

526
00:27:15,980 --> 00:27:16,820
Hongbing!

527
00:27:16,820 --> 00:27:18,090
Please come out, Hongbing!

528
00:27:18,090 --> 00:27:18,940
Tell him to leave.

529
00:27:19,640 --> 00:27:20,660
I don't want to see him.

530
00:27:31,880 --> 00:27:38,100
♪I always thought
once we see the full picture♪

531
00:27:41,180 --> 00:27:42,020
Mom.

532
00:27:42,020 --> 00:27:43,260
It's okay, Hui.

533
00:27:44,740 --> 00:27:45,820
Take good care of yourself.

534
00:27:49,020 --> 00:27:50,300
Don't make Dad angry anymore.

535
00:27:51,380 --> 00:27:52,220
I'm leaving now.

536
00:27:53,850 --> 00:27:59,250
♪Must have had more beautiful scenery♪

537
00:28:01,340 --> 00:28:07,610
♪Who knew the lights would dim,
and roads would take a turn♪

538
00:28:08,810 --> 00:28:14,890
♪That kites would drift
to places out of reach♪

539
00:28:16,130 --> 00:28:22,230
♪Who knew familiar silhouettes
would fade away♪

540
00:28:23,340 --> 00:28:28,960
♪And become
a distant place right by my side♪

541
00:28:30,780 --> 00:28:34,050
♪Keep moving forward
and don't look back♪

542
00:28:34,580 --> 00:28:37,550
♪The shore is only reached
by the road ahead♪

543
00:28:38,240 --> 00:28:41,010
♪Too much debt has accumulated♪

544
00:28:41,760 --> 00:28:44,550
♪In this short life♪

545
00:28:45,180 --> 00:28:46,740
(When you were little,)

546
00:28:46,740 --> 00:28:48,900
(I never even changed your diapers.)

547
00:28:51,300 --> 00:28:53,500
(Have you figured out
how to handle your mom?)

548
00:28:53,500 --> 00:28:54,510
(Just smooth things over.)

549
00:28:54,900 --> 00:28:55,740
Brilliant.

550
00:28:55,740 --> 00:28:56,900
Absolutely brilliant.

551
00:28:57,460 --> 00:28:58,300
You're a lifesaver.

552
00:29:02,100 --> 00:29:02,940
Dad.

553
00:29:04,210 --> 00:29:05,220
What are you doing here?

554
00:29:13,580 --> 00:29:15,220
Dad, why did you lock me up?

555
00:29:15,220 --> 00:29:16,060
You know exactly

556
00:29:16,060 --> 00:29:16,980
what you did.

557
00:29:18,120 --> 00:29:20,340
Will you only be satisfied
when you put me behind bars?

558
00:29:20,340 --> 00:29:21,180
It was me!

559
00:29:21,180 --> 00:29:22,900
Happy now? Are you satisfied?

560
00:29:23,060 --> 00:29:28,660
♪We could
understand each other with empathy♪

561
00:29:30,050 --> 00:29:36,540
♪I always thought
the path we never took♪

562
00:29:37,260 --> 00:29:38,460
Are you blind or what?

563
00:29:38,460 --> 00:29:42,590
♪Must have had more beautiful scenery♪

564
00:29:43,180 --> 00:29:44,020
Did you hear me?

565
00:29:44,460 --> 00:29:45,300
Say sorry.

566
00:29:45,300 --> 00:29:47,600
♪Keep moving forward
and don't look back♪

567
00:29:48,290 --> 00:29:51,550
♪The shore is only reached
by the road ahead♪

568
00:29:51,980 --> 00:29:54,780
♪Too much debt has accumulated♪

569
00:29:55,690 --> 00:29:58,570
♪In this short life♪

570
00:29:59,300 --> 00:30:02,670
♪Between right and wrong,
how to choose?♪

571
00:30:03,060 --> 00:30:06,080
♪Regret is inevitable in the end♪

572
00:30:06,590 --> 00:30:13,460
♪Even so-called love
is repaid with pain♪

573
00:30:13,910 --> 00:30:17,170
♪I hear the laughter
and follow the crowd♪

574
00:30:18,010 --> 00:30:21,220
♪Into the streets and alleys♪

575
00:30:21,540 --> 00:30:28,270
♪On that brightly lit night♪

576
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:32,270
♪Unfortunately, the breeze in town♪

577
00:30:32,800 --> 00:30:35,860
♪Can no longer catch up to the children♪

578
00:30:36,270 --> 00:30:39,340
♪Times have changed♪

579
00:30:39,820 --> 00:30:41,930
♪Now, everything♪

580
00:30:41,930 --> 00:30:42,780
Wang.

581
00:30:43,700 --> 00:30:44,540
Hui.

582
00:30:47,700 --> 00:30:48,540
I made the call.

583
00:30:49,510 --> 00:30:50,460
The guy is lying inside.

584
00:30:51,720 --> 00:30:52,700
I threw the first punch.

585
00:31:21,340 --> 00:31:22,340
I feel like

586
00:31:22,340 --> 00:31:24,220
we still need to
let Hongbing know about this.

587
00:31:24,860 --> 00:31:25,700
What do you think?

588
00:31:26,340 --> 00:31:27,660
Hongbing cares about his pride

589
00:31:28,580 --> 00:31:29,500
more than anything.

590
00:31:32,780 --> 00:31:34,460
If he finds out about this,

591
00:31:35,620 --> 00:31:36,800
he won't be able to handle it.

592
00:31:36,950 --> 00:31:38,740
True, but I know him.

593
00:31:39,860 --> 00:31:40,900
He's not that fragile.

594
00:31:41,620 --> 00:31:43,430
Precisely because
he cares about his pride

595
00:31:43,660 --> 00:31:44,500
and is responsible,

596
00:31:44,500 --> 00:31:45,820
he won't hide from this.

597
00:31:53,300 --> 00:31:54,980
My mind is a complete mess right now.

598
00:31:55,920 --> 00:31:57,500
I really don't know what to do anymore.

599
00:31:58,660 --> 00:31:59,500
Okay.

600
00:31:59,500 --> 00:32:00,340
Don't worry.

601
00:32:01,100 --> 00:32:01,940
I'll go check on him.

602
00:32:10,820 --> 00:32:11,660
Hongbing.

603
00:32:12,060 --> 00:32:13,420
I think there's something

604
00:32:13,420 --> 00:32:14,460
you need to know.

605
00:32:16,220 --> 00:32:17,620
Hui got into a fight

606
00:32:17,620 --> 00:32:19,340
at the dance hall last night.

607
00:32:19,340 --> 00:32:20,660
He beat someone up.

608
00:32:20,660 --> 00:32:22,460
The case has been
brought to the station.

609
00:32:23,340 --> 00:32:24,980
He might be detained for a few days.

610
00:32:29,780 --> 00:32:30,620
Hongbing?

611
00:32:31,540 --> 00:32:32,380
Hongbing?

612
00:32:34,540 --> 00:32:35,660
Pull yourself together

613
00:32:35,660 --> 00:32:36,660
as soon as you can.

614
00:32:37,060 --> 00:32:37,900
I'm heading out.

615
00:32:50,660 --> 00:32:51,500
Director Tong.

616
00:32:52,540 --> 00:32:53,380
Wait for me.

617
00:33:05,820 --> 00:33:06,700
How did Hui...

618
00:33:08,860 --> 00:33:09,860
How did Hui

619
00:33:09,860 --> 00:33:10,980
end up like this?

620
00:33:17,580 --> 00:33:18,700
Don't be sad.

621
00:33:18,700 --> 00:33:19,900
I'm here.

622
00:33:19,900 --> 00:33:20,780
Don't worry.

623
00:33:42,420 --> 00:33:43,260
Dad.

624
00:33:44,100 --> 00:33:44,940
You finally came out.

625
00:33:46,900 --> 00:33:48,540
That fight really did the trick.

626
00:33:49,740 --> 00:33:50,580
Why did you fight?

627
00:33:51,620 --> 00:33:53,540
I didn't want to see you
locked up in your room.

628
00:33:54,140 --> 00:33:54,980
You...

629
00:33:55,540 --> 00:33:56,660
You've changed so much,

630
00:33:59,380 --> 00:34:00,740
I barely recognize you anymore.

631
00:34:05,700 --> 00:34:06,700
Once you're in there,

632
00:34:07,020 --> 00:34:08,380
you'll have half a month.

633
00:34:09,580 --> 00:34:10,580
Use that time to reflect.

634
00:34:11,060 --> 00:34:11,900
Dad.

635
00:34:13,460 --> 00:34:14,580
No matter what I do,

636
00:34:16,220 --> 00:34:17,180
I've never once wanted

637
00:34:17,180 --> 00:34:18,020
to hurt you and Mom.

638
00:34:20,060 --> 00:34:22,220
Don't ever come home
to disgust me again.

639
00:34:22,220 --> 00:34:23,060
Get in the car.

640
00:34:25,380 --> 00:34:26,220
Dad.

641
00:34:26,540 --> 00:34:27,380
Big guy.

642
00:35:11,180 --> 00:35:17,260
♪I always thought
once we see the full picture♪

643
00:35:18,580 --> 00:35:24,420
♪We could
understand each other with empathy♪

644
00:35:25,980 --> 00:35:32,420
♪I always thought
the path we never took♪

645
00:35:33,140 --> 00:35:38,740
♪Must have had more beautiful scenery♪

646
00:35:40,580 --> 00:35:43,940
♪Keep moving forward
and don't look back♪

647
00:35:44,300 --> 00:35:47,540
♪The shore is only reached
by the road ahead♪

648
00:35:47,940 --> 00:35:50,820
♪Too much debt has accumulated♪

649
00:35:51,700 --> 00:35:54,580
♪In this short life♪

650
00:35:55,380 --> 00:35:59,020
♪Between right and wrong,
how to choose?♪

651
00:35:59,100 --> 00:36:02,580
♪Regret is inevitable in the end♪

652
00:36:02,740 --> 00:36:09,380
♪Even so-called love
is repaid with pain♪

653
00:36:09,860 --> 00:36:13,820
♪I hear the laughter
and follow the crowd♪

654
00:36:14,020 --> 00:36:17,260
♪Into the streets and alleys♪

655
00:36:17,500 --> 00:36:24,340
♪On that brightly lit night♪

656
00:36:25,060 --> 00:36:28,620
♪Unfortunately, the breeze in town♪

657
00:36:28,820 --> 00:36:32,380
♪Can no longer catch up to the children♪

658
00:36:32,380 --> 00:36:35,500
♪Times have changed♪

659
00:36:35,900 --> 00:36:38,300
♪Now, everything♪

660
00:36:38,980 --> 00:36:43,140
♪Is no longer what it used to be♪
